The father gave him a food bar-containing figs. Almost immediately after receiving this he developed very prominent congestion. The father noted that he began to develop a rash on the face and had significant redness of the eyes and profuse rhinorrhea. Father immediately returned to the office for evaluation. This child does have a history of having had a positive very weak RAST test to eggs, but tolerates eating eggs without difficulty. He has not had difficulties with influenza vaccine. He had very similar reaction in the past to contact with a latex balloon, developing the nasal symptoms, cough and rash.
HISTORY: Adverse Rxn/Allergies - Penicillin; Probable latex allergy with face swelling and gagging when exposed to a balloon; Mild anaphylactic like rxn 9/4/15 after varicella vaccine and eating a fig bar; Undefined dysmorphic syndrome (possible CHARGE association); Cleft lip and palate, status post repair; S/P tracheostomy for tracheomalacia versus subglottic stenosis/resolved; VSD w/partial spontaneous closure; Hypogonadism/Micro phallus/rx w Testosterone; Developmental delays/communication disorder; Sensorineural deafness/Congenital absence of the semicircular canals; Cochlear implant; Reactive airway disease; S/P myringotomy and tube placement; Gastrostomy, S/P Nissen fundoplication, GE Reflux - resolved; Ataxic Cerebral Palsy; Autism

SYMPTOM_TEXT: He developed a fever and full body rash/hives on 9/29/2013 and the rash/hives lasted for over 10 days Then his health and immune system quickly deteriorated. On 10/15/13 he developed candida diaper rash and impetigo. On 11/11/13 he developed a sleep disorder and feeding problems. On 12/17/13 he developed his first ear infection, on 1/9/14 he contracted the flu, on 2/21/14 he developed a second ear infection, and on 3/12/14 he developed a third ear infection. On 3/17/14 his stool changed. On 3/24/14 he developed a fourth ear infection and on 3/25/14 a fever.  In March and early April of 2014 he lost his eye contact, stopped responding to his name and stopped saying all the words he knew at the time including (Mama and Daddy). He started developing ritualistic and exclusive behavior likes lining up his cars and tuning out everyone around him. On 5/3/13 he developed a fifth ear infection, on 5/7/13 he had vomiting, on 5/15/13 he contracted hand, foot and mouth disease, and on 5/17/13 he had sores in mouth and difficulty swallowing. He continues to have a weakened immune system and in Dec. 2014 was diagnosed with Autism after 9 months of waiting for appointments for an evaluation and diagnosis of his condition.

This is a literature marketed report received from the authors of a published article, concerning a 15 year old male patient who was born by vaginal delivery after a full-term uncomplicated gestation. He was noted to have an undescended testis. He received diagnoses of gastroesophageal reflux disease and failure to thrive at infancy, followed by type 1 diabetes mellitus (at 2 years of age), primary hypothyroidism (at 4 years of age), mild speech delay, learning disabilities, recurrent infections (including sinusitis, streptococcal pharyngitis and pneumonias), nocturia and leukoplakia of the tongue. At 2 years of age, he underwent genetic evaluation at another hospital, and the chromosomes were reportedly normal. When the patient was 10 years of age, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the head was performed because of chronic headaches and nausea. The images showed numerous nonspecific, nonenhancing lesions (measure no more than 8 mm in diameter) in the bilateral periventricular and corona radiata white matter. Results of magnetic resonance angiography were normal. The complete blood count, erythrocyte sedimentation rate, levels of vitamin B12 and C-reactive protein, and antinuclear antibody titers were reportedly normal. A monospot test was negative, as was testing for Lyme disease and DNA for CADASIL (cerebral autosomal dominant arteriopathy with subcortical infarcts and leukoencephalopathy). The patient was seen by neurologists at a second hospital; he reportedly had no seizure disorder. When the patient was 13 years of age, laboratory testing revealed normal blood levels of total protein and albumin. Between 13 years 6 months of age and 14 years 6 months of age, the patient's prothrombin-time international normalized ratio, lipid profile, and red-cell osmotic fragility were normal, as were blood levels of ceruloplasmin, iron, iron-binding capacity, IgG, and glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (G6PD) and the 24-hour urinary copper level. A Coombs' test screening for celiac disease and Heinz bodies and tests for hepatitis B and C viruses, antinuclear antibodies, anti-liver-kidney microsomal antibodies, and F-actin smooth-muscle antibodies were negative. Hemoglobin electrophoresis revealed 97.3% hemoglobin A, and 2.3% hemoglobin A2. Ophthalmologic examination revealed no evidence of retinopathy. The patient was referred to the gastroenterology clinic of this hospital. The patient had a history of inguinal herniorrhaphies and had undergone orchidopexy at 15 months of age. He also had had orthopedic injuries related to sports traumas. Results of a sweat test (performed at 18 months of age), a bone-age study (at 20 months of age), and a tongue biopsy (at 12 years of age) were reportedly normal. Medications included insulin (by pump) and levothyroxine (manufacturer unknown). He had no known allergies to medications. He attended special-education classes in high school and lived with his parents and siblings. A maternal uncle had been born prematurely and had a history of learning disabilities, developmental delay, hypogammaglobulinemia (that required infusions of intravenous immune globulin), cryptogenic cirrhosis (that had been diagnosed when he was 30 years of age and was complicated by the hepatopulmonary syndrome), splenic-artery aneurysms, type 1 diabetes mellitus, and bone marrow failure; he died in his 40's. A maternal great-grandmother was reported to have scleroderma that had developed when she was in her 80s, his paternal grandmother had type 1 diabetes mellitus that had developed when she was in her teens, his mother had Graves' disease, his father had non-insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus, and his teenage siblings were healthy. On examination, the patient had slight facial dysmorphism. His height was in the 32nd percentile, and his weight in the 33rd percentile. There was a white plaque with shallow ulceration on the tongue. The abdomen was soft and nondistended, with a palpable spleen three fingerbreadths below the l

October 5, 2015 Vaccinations for flu and pneumonia at dr. office, both injections in left arm. October 6, 2015 Can not move left arm, very painful, can barely walk, left leg does not seem to work well, almost fell on way to bathroom. Felt as if I has no control of the movements of the left side of my body. No change for 7 days as I spent all the time in a recliner. October 14, 2015 Can now lift my left arm approximately 6 inches, left leg is beginning to work but does not synchronize with my right leg while trying to walk. Soles of feet have stinging sensations constantly and skin feels as if it is being poked with needles. My right side is starting to respond similarly to my left side. My arms feel as if they are asleep for a couple hours at a time. Sometimes hands and feet will tingle for an hour or so. I have no sensation in my fingertips, I can not feel things. My fingernails have broken to the quick and are not growing. October 30, 2015 I can lift my arms high enough to put on shirts, but is very painful. My left arm hurts constantly. Nov. 11, 2015 My legs seem to work together  a little better. There have been two instances when everything seemed to be working fairly well and without ant warning both legs just seemed almost paralyzed. One time I was at market and did not think I could get to my car in the parking lot. This frightened me so much that I now carry a folding cane at all times. Nov. 16, 2015 I had a dr. appointment today. The dr. had an intern student on staff that day. She was sent in to see me. I was in terrible condition and I told her about all of my symptoms. She talked with me for about 30 minutes. She recorded all of the information into the computer. The dr. entered the room and stated that this was going to be a short visit- Do you need any medication refills? He did not examine me, I question his examination report for that day. Nov. 22, 2015 I am now having bladder problems. I can not keep my urine stream going. It is difficult to start urinating, and then the flow stops, sometimes I start and stop urinating 9-10 times before I can empty my bladder. This occurs event if  my bladder seems very full. I have never had this problem previously and I have not had any medication changes. It is a struggle to ensure that I get my bladder empty. Today I went to the bathroom, when I pulled down my pants I was surprised to discover that I had soiled my pants. It was very runny, I had not passed gas, I did not know it had happened. Now I fear it will happen when  I am not home. Dec. 6, 2015 I think I have a bladder infection, but a trip to the dr. and a urine test does not indicate an infection. Even though I have had muscular pain for a few years, all of the new pains are completely different. I hope these new pains recede soon as I just seem to be getting weak and do not seem to be seeing any improvement. I have started physical therapy, trying to improve my legs. Jan. 6, 2016 I had an MRI today, to check for any physical reason that my bladder does not work correctly. Nothing was identified on the MRI.
HISTORY: Anxiety; Hip pain; Swelling musculoskeletal pain

49 yo female who developed a new onset seizure disorder while out of the country with temporal association to vaccine receipt of anthrax and influenza vaccine (neither vaccine is documented). The first documented seizure episode occurred on 19 OCT 2012 and a prior undocumented suspected seizure may have occurred 6-8 weeks earlier in late August or early September 2012. She reports she received anthrax vaccine prior to the August/September event and influenza vaccine within 1 day of the October event. Her October seizure event occurred while in a class, was witnessed and history and evaluation is well documented. The patient experienced tonic clonic activity of arms, legs and trunk for 3 minutes (estimated) causing fall from chair to ground and the incident description states "her head struck the surface of the desk and she sustained a large forehead contusion and developed a large facial bruise leaving the patient with bilateral raccoon eyes and the facial hematoma." She demonstrated a postictal state and only responded to painful stimuli for 5-10 minutes. She had no documented incontinence but tongue biting occurred. There were no identified provoking circumstances. She had no self or family history of seizures. She had a normal non-contrast brain CT (no MRI due to stent history), urine drug screen, CBC and chemistry panel. She initially complained of headache which was subsequently consistently documented, and of memory loss. She was medically evacuated to another location where she was evaluated by neurology, noted to have a normal neurological exam and a normal EEG. She was returned to a third location and a repeat awake and sleep EEG demonstrated on 30 Oct 2015 was abnormal and consistent with focal epileptiform discharges. This is less likely to be vaccine related.
LAB_DATA: EEG, 24 OCT 2015, WNL; EEG, 30 OCT 2012, + epiliptiform discharges
HISTORY: LCA spinal dissection X5 stents 1996; hypothyroidism

I'm going to take you back to 2006 when my MD, at that time, gave me a pneumonia and tetanus shot in the upper section of my left arm. There was no pain; needle marks; redness; or after affects. I have not had a cold in nine (9) years. Now, I have been cursed!! When I asked for a pneumonia shot, my MD was not the person who administered the shot; who, at no time, explained in full detail what the consequences of the strength of this pneumonia shot would be. The shot was given as follows: The needle was inserted into top of my left shoulder, and it stung. Then, it turned red! When I arrived home, the upper section of my left arm turned RED! It hurt, and there was pain. I put alcohol on the area. In a few days the redness evaporated, but the arm was achy, ad then there was pain. I did contact the doctor's office when the arm turned red, and was told to call back if it became worse. It did get worse. I spoke to Dr., and told him there was pain and severe headaches. He also stated to call him back, if it got worse. I asked him if I could get a stroke or heart attack. He stated: "No." The third call I made was to schedule an appointment with Dr. He suggested an x-ray of my left arm. The results were: beginning of arthritis!! He did mention to take ADVIL twice a day and some light exercise. This is what I eventually took to relieve the pressure and pain: ADVIL or TYLENOL light exercise heating pad. The existing conditions to this day are: Sniffles, runny nose, sneezing, achiness: Joint and muscle, Stiffness: neck; Shoulder, Back, Pain: neck; shoulder arm, headaches, tiredness. On Wednesday, 6 January 2016, a blood red spot appeared on the left side of my left eye. in four (4) days it disappeared. My other medical conditions are; High blood pressure, High cholesterol, Sinus condition, Arthritis. I am allergic to: Penicillin, aspirin, SUDAFED, Lisinopril, Lovastatin, PREVNAR 13. I did report this mele of circumstances to Health Plan, but was told that I only up to 60 days to report any backlash from P-13. I am still experiencing all the conditions listed in this letter. If I had bee given a clearer insight into P-13's shot, I would not have taken it. all medical personnel should thoroughly advise and give a better interpretation of what this pneumonia shot is capable of to all recipients. I am a senior who thought I was going into never-never land!! On Wednesday, 13 January 2016, I contacted Dr's office to have lab work done. The person I spoke with stated she would call me back. She did not. On Friday, 15 January 2016, I call again. She denied talking to me on the 13th. I stated again, about lab work, and she stated in April, I don't trust her. I hope Dr was contacted.
LAB_DATA: I have asked for lab tests - the earliest would be April.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Significant swelling at injection site, and in the opposite arm. Redness and hardness from the elbow to the shoulder of the arm that had the injection. 2 days after injection vision became blurry. 3 days after injection eyes were not focusing and my wife could see that both eyes were not looking in the same direction. 5 days after injection the eye blurriness stopped, although I had eye fatigue for a couple weeks. Severe fatigue and nausea from the day after injection was almost constant for 1 month. On August 12, one week after injection I had a fever of 100.5, and fatigue, and nausea. Doctor was called, and I was seen and tests were run. I was given an antibiotic for my sypmtoms (cough, nasal drainage, fever). After 3 days the fever subsided, and the fatigue and nausea persisted for about 3-5 weeks from the time of injection. About once a month, a rash appears on or around injection site of both arms since the injection of DTap acel. Severe fatigue still occurs for several weeks, followed by 1-2 weeks of more "normal" energy levels. Then, fatigue again continues with a slight rash on arms. This pattern has continued from the 2nd dose of DTaP on August 5, 2015 until present (January 2016).
HISTORY: 10 months post allogenic stem cell transplant for AML.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initial unsolicited misuse report received from a nurse on 13 January 2016. This case involves a 49-year-old female patient who was vaccinated with a first dose of ADACEL (batch number U5263AA, expiry date 21 January 2018, route of administration were not reported) in the left deltoid on 20 November 2015 instead of a dose of TENIVAC (batch number, expiry date, site and route of administration were not reported) on an unspecified date for the indication dog bite. Illness at time of vaccination was reported as none. Pre-existing physician diagnosed allergies included cat allergy and no birth defects and medical conditions were reported. Patient had no other vaccinations within four weeks of vaccinations. On 20 November 2015, few hours "same night" following the vaccination patient developed injection site pain in the left deltoid and continuous headache. On 4 December 2015, 14 days following the vaccination patient experienced awful taste in her mouth. On an unspecified date, following the vaccination "During the week of Christmas" patient experienced bilateral foot pain and since then she had numbness and tingling in bilateral hands and feet with intermittent pain. She was worried she may have an autoimmune disorder. It was a wrong vaccine administered case, as patient received ADACEL in error instead of TENIVAC vaccine. It was reported that she didn't want ADACEL as it contained extra chemicals that she did not need. Patient had no laboratory investigation. Corrective treatment was not reported. The outcome of events was not recovered for events bilateral foot pain, numbness, tingling in bilateral hands and feet with intermittent pain and autoimmune disorder and recovered from the events awful taste in her mouth (lasted for four days), injection site pain in the left deltoid (lasted for three days) and continuous headache (lasted for four days). Upon internal review, the company decided to consider the event serious because of important medical event: she may have an autoimmune disorder. List of documents held by sender: none.

Information has been received from a 58 year old male subject enrolled in a study. The subject's concurrent condition included allergic to penicillin manifested by rash, alcohol use (five mixed drinks per month), blood cholesterol increased, depression and herpes simplex. The subject's medical history included colitis ulcerative, chill, tremor, gastric disorder, clostridium difficile colitis and ex-tobacco user. The subject was previously on ENBREL for eight years and discontinued due to unspecified issues with ulcerative colitis; on REMICADE and discontinued due to rigors and sharp shaking; and also on SIMPONI from 2012 to 2013, experienced unspecified gastric issues and clostridium difficile. The subject was not on any biologics from August 2013 to July 2014. Concomitant therapies included VALTREX, citalopram, WELLBUTRIN, pravastatin, influenza virus vaccine (unspecified) and probiotics (unspecified). In July 2014 the subject started HUMIRA (Solution for injection in pre-filled syringe, 40 mg in 2 weeks, route unknown) for plaque psoriasis and psoriatic arthritis. In November 2014, the subject experienced ulcerative colitis flare. It was further described as abdominal pain, diarrhea and increased bowel movements. The events recovered without further treatment. In November 2014, the ulcerative colitis flare resolved. On unknown date in November 2014, he had a flu vaccine. Om 29-DEC-2014, he had PNEUMOVAX 23 (dose and route was not reported). On 29-DEC-2014, the subject experienced injection site pain on left arm. The event was resolved without further treatment. On the same date, the injection site pain on left arm was resolved. On 31-DEC-2014, the subject experienced nasal congestion, chest congestion, muscle aches, cold sweats and flu. On the same day, he experienced chills and general malaise. TYLENOL was taken as a treatment. On 10-JAN-2015, the nasal congestion, chest congestion, muscle aches, cold sweats and flu were resolved. On the same day chills and general malaise were also resolved. He felt that the flu was unrelated to HUMIRA. Action taken with PNEUMOVAX 23 regarding all events was not reported; action taken with HUMIRA regarding injection site pain on left arm, chest congestion, cold sweat and flu was reported as dose not change, regarding general malaise was not reported. The relationship between injection site pain on left arm with PNEUMOVAX 23 was reported as related, the relationship between chest congestion, general malaise, cold sweat and flu with PNEUMOVAX 23 was not reported. The relationship between injection site pain on left arm and general malaise with HUMIRA was not reported, the relationship between chest congestion, cold sweat and flu was reported as not related. Additional information is expected.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Information has been received from a 35 year old female patient with no drug reactions/allergies and no pertinent medical history for VARIVAX (Merck), a Pregnancy Registry product, who on 22-NOV-2011, was vaccinated with the first dose of VARIVAX (Merck) (route not reported). There was no concomitant medication. The same day, on 22-NOV-2011, a pregnancy test at the doctor's office was negative. The patient ovulated on 26-NOV-2011. A home pregnancy test on 10-DEC-2011 was positive. The patient repeated the home test and it was again negative. The patient telephoned the doctor and would see her on 13-DEC-2011. At the time of the report, the patient outcome was unknown. The last menstrual period was 12-NOV-2011. Estimated delivery date would be 18-AUG-2012. Follow-up information was received from the nurse practitioner on 25-JAN-2016. It was reported that the patient had undergone scheduled C-section (Caesarean section) (medically significant) at 35-36 weeks (premature delivery) of pregnancy and delivered a male infant weighing 3130 grams and 18 3/4 inches in length. The APGAR score was reported as 9/9 at 5 mins. No information was provided regarding the health status of the infant or congenital anomalies. The reason for the patient's scheduled C-section and she reported that the patient had a history of a Myomectomy in 2011 prior to vaccination. The outcome of the events caesarean section and the premature baby was reported as recovered. The relatedness of the events "scheduled C-section" and "premature delivery" with the suspect product VARIVAX (Merck) was unknown. Upon internal review the term "scheduled C-section" and "premature delivery" was considered as medically significant. The case was linked to another case via same parent child link. Additional information is not expected as no further information was not available. Events and narrative updated.
LAB_DATA: 11/22/2011, Pregnancy test, Negative; 12/10/2011, Pregnancy test, negative, comment: positive; 12/10/2011, Pregnancy test, positive, Comment: negative

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had a possible exposure to Rabies as there was a bat in my attic. This happened over Thanksgiving. I received Rabies immunoglobulin and a series of IMOVAX rabies vaccination shots over the course of December. My first shot was December 14, my last shot was December 29. After the immunoglobulin I began experiencing migratory arthralgia and myalgia.  By Christmas I began experiencing severe paresthesias and burning in my arms and legs. My muscles fatigue so easily I can hardly carry my handbag. After visits to Clinics, I finally found a neurologist who feels I have autoimmune related neuropathy secondary to the vaccination. I am on gabapentin, CYMBALTA, and ATIVAN with a very little relief of symptoms. I am devastated.
LAB_DATA: All of my blood work has been negative including test for Lyme disease, chemistry panels etc. My MRI of the brain and cervical spine was negative.
OTHER_MEDS: SYNTHROID; lorazepam; gabapentin; CYMBALTA; Vitamin B12
HISTORY: Hypothyroidism; Other than completely manageable asymptomatic hypothyroidism I have no known illnesses prior to this vaccine. I take 100 micrograms of SYNTHROID every day and have no symptoms prior to this vaccination I worked out every day and was totally healthy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1/26/16 Pt. came to the Imm. clinic to update immunizations related to his annual physical and job description. Pt. stated he began itching that evening and developed a rash on his rt. lower leg and left ankle. 1/28/16 Pt. alerted Imms clinic about the rash and itching. Pt. chose to see personal PCP after 1/28/16.
Redness, swelling, pain.
Pt developed varicella after 2 doses of vaccine.
Rt upper arm red firm at injection site itches, 8 out of 10 pain with arm movement. Referred to PMD.

Vaccine administration yesterday. Today she feels like she is getting a cold (sore throat). No trouble breathing, fever. Asked if she could take COLD-EEZE. 1-18-16 - pt. called today feeling back to normal but noticed rash on back. No pain. No itching. Encouraged her to see PMD.
Prolonged uncontrollable crying and irritability greater than or equal to 3 hrs.
Pt. was given Tdap on 1/11/16 - arm started having redness and irritation 5 days post shot peaked at 7 days post shot - warm compresses. Advised to call if worse.

Hives and bruising on legs. Hives on arms - back - breast - face. Eyelids and lips had some swelling. 3 time on prednisone 10 mg. - 1 ZANTAC - 1 all day allergy pill in A.M. and 1-2 BENADRYL in P.M. Saw dermatologist Dec. 30/15. Said hives were from shot. Prescribed - fluocinonide cream .05%. Ongoing.
Pt develops red bumps about 3 quarters. A little painful at the site.

Patient cries inconsolably for 3 or more nights after receiving her childhood vaccinations. It has worsened after each round. This happens 3-5 days after immunizations, and lasts for 3-5 hours every night.

Could not lift arm from side, pain affected sleep (amount and duration). X-ray revealed no fractures, separation. After 7 days no improvement received cortisone shot, one day later pain much better and could raise arm 90 degrees from body.

Information has been received from the authors in a published literature article, regarding 5 (also reported as 17% of 28 patients) adolescent or young adult patients of unknown age and gender with perinatally acquired human immunodeficiency virus (PAH). On an unknown date, the patients were vaccinated with a dose of MMR (Manufacturer unknown) (Lot number, expiration date, strength, dose and frequency were not provided). Concomitant medication was not reported. On an unknown date, despite appropriate prior vaccination, the patient experienced measles non-immunity which was defined as IgG titers < 120 miU by plaque reduction neutralization (PRN) assay and < 0.70 IU by measles enzyme immunoassay (EIA) (vaccination failure and seroconversion test negative). The outcome of vaccination failure and seroconversion test negative was unknown at the time of the report. The reporter considered vaccination failure and seroconversion test negative to be related to MMR (manufacturer unknown). This is one of several reports from the same source (MARRS# 1601USA010845, 1601USA010935, 1601USA010936). Additional information has been requested.
LAB_DATA: PRN (On unknown date) results: Nonimmune (negative). Measles immunity was defined as IgG titers > 120 miU by PRN assay and >0.70 IU by EIA.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This spontaneous case report was received from a nurse practitioner regarding a male child currently with a current age of 3 years. It was reported that the child was exposed to the VARIVAX (Merck) via, transplacental route as the patient's mother received the vaccine during her 1st trimester. The baby was born at 35-36 week (Premature baby 33 to 36 weeks) (medically significant). The child weight was reported as 3130 grams and height was 18 3/3 inches at the time of birth. I was referred to a rheumatologist who increased the Prednisone treatment to 40mg. This suppressed the pain by about 80%. After about 1-2 weeks at that dosage, I started a reduced dosage to wean me from the Prednisone and at the same time was prescribed a progressively increased amount of Gabapentin over about a three week period. SYMPTOM_TEXT: After two individual Prevnar 13 shots, a toddler experienced foul-smelling poop and diarrhea and a very bad diaper rash with red raised bumps for 5 days. A previously unvaccinated, breastfed girl was given 2 doses of Prevnar13 (a full series of two shots since it was delayed). The first was at age 12 months (10/30/15), and the second was at age 15 months (01/22/2016).  Her health and temperature at both visits were normal, and there were no diet or diapering changes before or after either visit. About one day after the 10/15 shot, she experienced foul-smelling poop. There were about 2 poops in one day that had less water than usual, then later that day or the next day there were about 3 soft (but not fully runny) foul-smelling poops every 2-3 hours. The parents believed it was a coincidence, and the girl showed no other symptoms apart from slight tiredness, that may have been unrelated. She was treated at home with almond oil, A&D, baths, air drying, and Triple Paste. While the rash was painful and bright red the first day, the next day it turned into red raised bumps from anus to genitals that lasted about 2-3 days. As it showed improvement and seemed to not be painful after the first day of discovery, she was treated at home, and the rash was fully gone at the end of a week. The same symptoms (but with more severity) happened after her 1/22 shot. This time, the foul-smelling runny poops started the morning of the 23rd, and there were about 4-5 of them, one every 2 hours. The rash this time, however, was more severe. After the first runny poop (the morning of the 23rd), a larger diaper area turned bright solid red, and she screamed and cried when it was touched. By the 24th, the rash again turned into bright red raised bumps (very numerous and close together) from anus to genitals, spreading out to inner thigh, but there was no more diarrhea or signs of her discomfort. The bright red color was gone by the morning of the 27th, and the rash was gone fully by the 28th. Again, she showed slight signs of tiredness, but no other symptoms. Lastly, the parents primarily cloth diaper, and the father reported that his clothes severely itched him on the 26th. They wondered if this was because the clothes he was wearing were washed in a separate load after a diaper load from the 25th. However, they do not know if the itchy clothes are related directly to Prevnar 13, as it could easily be unrelated.

My wife went to the local pharmacy to get the PREVNAR13 vaccine based on the advice of our primary care doctor. She took the PREVNAR13 shot in the arm about noon on December 17, 2015. We went home had lunch, watched TV, and talked awhile until she decided to take a nap. About 5:45 P.M. that evening, I went to the bedroom to wake her up and I returned to another room. I went back to check on her twice until the third time of no response; I tried to get her to get out of bed. She was not responsive to my directions, disoriented, and confused. At this time, I called 911 for an ambulance. When the medics arrived her body temperature was 101.5 F degrees. I told them about the vaccine that she had earlier that day. They gave her TYLENOL and started an IV and took her to hospital. At hospital she was treated in the ER after drawing blood and getting urine samples. About 10:00 P.M. the nurse said that she had some type of infection. While in the ER she was given MOTRIN and various antibiotics (ZOYSN). It was decided later that she needed to be admitted for at least one day. About 1:20 A.M. December 18, 2015, she was admitted into the ICU Unit for treatment. Patient was treated here at hospital from 12/17/2015-12/28/2015. My first meeting with Dr. we talked about why she was brought to the hospital and her medical history. During the time she was at this hospital her medical diagnosis and conditions were changed several times such as rapid heart rate, unknown virus, rhinovirus, atrial fibrillation, fluid in lungs, high blood pressure 189/107, bleeding mouth, blood in the urine, low blood count, diffused pneumonia, and common cold. Numerous lab test were done while she was being treated here. She was also given blood while she was here. During my visits with patient, I have noticed that she is having difficulty remembering things. It appears that this may be as ongoing problem. On December 28, 2015, she was transferred to another hospital. Patient was cared for from 12/28/15-01/11/2016. While at hospital, she continued treatments to clear the fluids in the lungs and started the initial physical and occupational therapies. On January 11, 2016, she was transferred to Skilled Nursing and Rehabilitation. During her stay here, she is receiving her follow-up medications for the heart and lungs. She is also doing occupational and physical therapy. The Nurse Practitioner has noticed that patient is having memory issues. Last week, the nurse practitioner asked me about her memory and if it was like it is now before she became sick or if it is worse. It is possible that, she may be released to go home next week after this long ordeal.
LAB_DATA: Various tests run during hospital stay

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This case was reported by a consumer via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of psychotic episode in a female patient who received Influenza vaccine. Co-suspect products included aripiprazole for schizophrenia and Tetanus vaccine. Previously administered products included HALDOL with an associated reaction of alopecia and PROLIXIN with an associated reaction of alopecia. Concurrent medical conditions included schizophrenia. In 2015, the patient received Influenza vaccine. On an unknown date, the patient started aripiprazole at an unknown dose and frequency. In 2015, the patient received Tetanus vaccine. In 2015, an unknown time after receiving Influenza vaccine, the patient experienced psychotic episode (serious criteria hospitalization) and drug interaction. On an unknown date, the outcome of the psychotic episode was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the drug interaction was unknown. It was unknown if the reporter considered the psychotic episode and drug interaction to be related to Influenza vaccine. Additional details were received as follows: The patient's medical history includes HALDOL and PROLIXIN which lead to alopecia, hair growing slowly and thinning hair. In 2014, the patient started to receive ABILIFY MAINTENA (400 mg) with unknown frequency. It was unknown if it was single vial or dual chamber. The sample was not available as it was administered. It was unknown if the ABILIFY MAINTENA was administered by a healthcare professional. The site of administration was unknown.  It was unknown if the dose was 1st dose or the dates of the previous doses were unknown. It was unknown if the doses were prepared according to the prescribing information (PI) and reference guide. It was unknown if any physical defects were noted during preparation of product or in the kit. It was unknown if there were any unusual observations noted during administration. In 2015, the patient started ABILIFY (30 mg) daily for unknown indication. The patient reported that, ABILIFY MAINTENA worked great for her as in, it got her thinking going and she became relaxed and felt overall well mentally. On an unknown date, she began experiencing thinning hair, hair growing slowly and alopecia. In 2015, the patient received Influenza vaccine and Tetanus vaccine. It was reported that, Influenza and Tetanus vaccines diluted the ABILIFY MAINTENA out of her blood, which was also described as the vaccines lessened the ABILIFY MAINTENA in her blood. When ABILIFY MAINTENA, was diluted, the patient's hair got healthier. In late October 2015 or early November 2015, the patient had psychotic episode because ABILIFY MAINTENA was diluted out of her system and she was subsequently admitted to the hospital, where she started to receive ABILIFY 30 mg daily and ABILIFY MAINTENA was not given in the hospital. The patient reported that, ABILIFY made her extremely hungry and made her feel depressed and it was unknown if there was any relevant data. The patient was not receiving ABILIFY MAINTENA at the time of reporting. At the time of reporting, the thinning hair, hair growing slowly and alopecia were recovering. The reporter denied the consent to be contacted for follow up. So, no further information was available.
HISTORY: HALDOL, Product used for unknown indication, Alopecia; PROLIXIN, Product used for unknown indication, Alopecia

This is a spontaneous report from a Pfizer-sponsored program from a contactable consumer. A 68-years-old female patient received PREVNAR 13 (NDC number: 000051971-05), via an unspecified route of administration in the right arm on 31Dec2015 at 0.5 ml single. Medical history included ongoing seizure; hurt her left leg from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing. The patient had x-ray of head a long time before when first began having seizures, maybe 30 years before, which showed black spot on left side of her head. It didn't go all the way down into her brain, hadn't grown, no explanation why it was there. Thought to be the cause of her seizures. The patient previously took PREVNAR 13 about 10 years before and experienced no adverse event. Concomitant medication included DILANTIN for seizure. Patient used to be on 200 mg in the morning and 200 mg in the evening until about six months before when she had her phenytoin level checked and it was too high. At that time, she decreased her dose to 100mg one in the morning and 200 mg at night. On 01Jan2016 at 18:00 the patient had seizure which the patient believed was due to the PREVNAR 13. They were at a friend's house, her friend knew she was having a seizure because she grabbed the card table she was eating off of, was shaking it, and her friend could not get reporter's hand off of it. Has history of accident in which she hurt her left leg. Thought she hurt it again during the seizure as it was still sore. They called the ambulance to take her to emergency room, where she spent 18 hours. The patient was happy enough to walk to the ambulance to go. While at hospital, they attempted to release her on three different occasions. They started to release her the first time, but she couldn't walk so they kept her. Next time they told her she was free to go, she couldn't speak so they kept her. Next time they said they were keeping her for more tests, did EKG and heart ultrasound, which came back fine on 02Jan2016. An head scan on 02Jan2016 was normal. The patient also had lab work on the same date, including phenytoin level, which showed she had no phenytoin in her system because she had been without her phenytoin for 18 hours. After this seizure, she increased her phenytoin (NDC: 0071036924, Lot: M38474, EXP: July2017) to 200 mg in the morning and 200 mg in the evening. The patient recovered with sequel from seizure on the same date. A 24 year old woman received MassBiologics Td vaccine (Lot# A080A) in the left deltoid on 9/16/15 for wound prophylaxis.  The following day she reported she felt warm to the touch and developed itching, swelling, and pain at the injection site.  Two days after the immunization (9/18/15), she contacted her health care provider to report these symptoms along with expansion of the pruritus to her hand as well as hand stiffness.  Following the adverse event, she took ibuprofen 600mg orally.  The patient was offered an evaluation by her health care provider, but she declined. Sender's Comments: This adverse event is assessed as non-serious and labeled, as injection site reactions including pain, pruritus, and swelling are described in the product labeling, as is pyrexia (which may have caused the patient to feel "warm to the touch").  It is possible the reported hand stiffness was due to musculoskeletal stiffness (reaction described in the package insert) or was secondary to the swelling in the affected limb, but this is unable to be confirmed as the patient declined an evaluation by the provider on the day the symptoms were reported.  MassBiologics performed a follow up with the health care provider on two occasions as summarized below: Follow-up on 10/14/15:  The reporter informed that the patient did not visit the physician since the adverse event and that the clinic had not heard from the patient since she last called to report the event. The reporter also mentioned that the patient was scheduled for a visit on the 29th of October. Follow-up on 10/30/15:  The reporter informed that the patient had failed to keep her appointment at the physician's office. Patient's recovery status is unknown. All attempts to obtain additional information have been unsuccessful.
HISTORY: Patient was reported to be allergic to the following: azithromycin, macrolide antibiotics, grass, pollen, rye

AFTER THE PATIENT GOT THE VACCINE 5 MINUTES LATER, HE STATED FEELING DIZZY, I PROVIDED HIM THE AMMONIA INHALANTS AND FAINTED. I WAS HOLDING HIS HAND AND I LAY HIM ON THE FLOOR. PATIENT DID NOT HIT HIS HEAD. HE PASSED OUT FOR ONE MINUTE. 911 ARRIVED AND CHECKED HIS VITALS AND WAS FINE.
LAB_DATA: 911 CHECKED HIS VITALS AND HE WAS FINE

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Coughing, no other sypmtoms. No trouble breathing. Cough resolved with Benadryl.
Incredibly fussy after vaccine. Developed eczema 1 week later and a very bad cold/cough a few days after that. Eczema is still present.

Patient was vaccinated with Human Papillomavirus 9-valent Vaccine, Meningococcal Conjugate vaccine and the Inactivated Influenza vaccine. The patient sat and was monitored for the recommended 15 minutes after the immunizations and did not show any symptoms of adverse reactions.  As the patient was getting ready to leave, she began to feel lightheaded and was assisted to lie in Trendelenburg position, the patient's symptoms began to resolve after about 5 minutes. The patient drank 6 ounces of apple juice and was then able to sit up, without return of lightheadedness or any other symptoms.  Vital signs were stable (blood pressure 136/82, pulse 73), and patient's condition returned to the same as it was prior to vaccination. Patient was then discharged to home. Patient was advised to get plenty of rest, drink adequate oral fluids and refrain from over-exertion and strenuous activities for the next several hours. Patient was advised for future vaccination, she should lie down prior to and for 15 minutes after the vaccinations.
OTHER_MEDS: Ibuprofen [MOTRIN] 200 mg tablet 1-2 tablets by mouth every 6 hours as needed for pain.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came back to the pharmacy almost a month after vaccination still complaining of soreness of the arm. No redness, no swelling, no bruising, no range of motion issue. Just tenderness.

Nausea, blacked out after injection, constant pain in arm, numbness that comes and goes, diminished muscle strength and control, joint pain, seizures the night of injection, fever, regular migraines.  All but seizures, fever, and blackouts are still ongoing.

This spontaneous report as received from a physician refers to a 59 year old female patient with a positive history of herpes simplex. It was reported that the patient  had multiple (3 to 4) outbreaks per year (maximum of 7 under extremes of sun exposure or stress) since an unknown date, reported as since the age of 17. The patient did not have any outbreaks of shingles, but had chickenpox as a child at the age of 6 or 7 (date unspecified). The patient stated that the chickenpox was severe with whole body pocks, though no hospitalization, pneumonia, seizures or encephalitis was involved. The patient did not use any prophylactic medication, but she used acyclovir pills and acyclovir ointment as treatment for individual outbreaks of herpes simplex. She had never had a genital herpes outbreak. On an unknown date in 2013, the patient was vaccinated with a dose of ZOSTAVAX injection (dose, route of administration, lot # and expiry date were not reported). There were no concomitant therapies reported. The physician reported that the patient's herpes simplex cold sores did not return over the last two  years after the patients were vaccinated with ZOSTAVAX (onset date approximately in 2013). She had zero outbreaks since she had the vaccine. The patient stated that her sister-in-law had the same effect after her vaccination with ZOSTAVAX (captured in MARRS#1512USA001048). The physician stated that this occurrence might be "just a fluke" and there was no way of knowing the causality. All telephone attempts to obtain follow up information had been unsuccessful. This is one of two reports received from the same reporter. Additional information has been requested.

This spontaneous report as received from a registered nurse refers to a 20 year old female patient. The patient's concurrent condition included allergy to latex. On 13-JUL-2009, the patient had a second measles, mumps, and rubella titer which results "equivocal". The patient had a third measles, mumps and rubella titer drawn on 21-DEC-2015 which resulted "negative for measles but not mumps and rubella". It was reported that the patient has not received any additional doses of M-M-R II after any of the three titers that were drawn. The outcome of measles antibody negative was reported as not recovered/not resolved. The outcome of rubella negative and mumps antibody tests negative was reported as recovered/resolved on 21-DEC-2015. The relatedness between the events and M-M-R II was not reported. Additional information has been requested.

High fever 104.5 four days after vaccination this continued to go up and down for 1 week. He was lethargic with fever. He had turned gray/greenish color and almost passed out - 6 days after vaccine. He had loose stools - low energy. His arm muscles were twitching with the fever. He had low white blood cell count. March 19, 2007 - varicella (VARIVAX) was administered - this was the only vaccine given at this well child appointment. March 23, 2007 - I called doctor's office because of high fever 104.5, lethargy and his arm muscles were twitching  - asked if this was a reaction to this vaccine. Doctor said it wasnt' typical of the vaccine said to make an appointment to be seen. March 27, 2007 - office visit doctor said not typical of vaccine but she also said she didn't know what was really going on. Doctor prescribed Amoxicillin in case there was something bacterial going on. (When I called to get these dates I was also told the doctor had a diagnosis of an ear infection in the right ear as the reason for prescribing the Amoxicillin. In my actual conversation with the doctor she said absolutely nothing about an ear infection, the only thing she said was she didn't know exactly, but to try an antibiotic in case it was something bacterial - no mention of ear infection). March 27, 2007 ordered 1st of 4 labs/blood test. March 28, 2007 phone call w/results indicated very low white blood cell count - 2.8. Doctor changed diagnosis to "viral". April 3 and 4, 2007 labs and results of labs - white blood cell count at 3.9. April 17, 2007 3rd lab test - white blood cell count at 4.0. June 3, 2007 4th lab results white blood cell count. I also reported this situation to the Health Department. In the process of all of these weeks and months of doctor office visits and blood work/labs we also sought help from a chiropractor who also recommended a immune boosting standard process IMMUNUPLEX supplement which we gave our son during this time to help boost his immune system. To our knowledge he did make a full recovery from this event. This has been a very frustrating situation for our family. With all that happened the doctor's office was in this denial that it had anything to do with this vaccine because "it didn't happen within the "normal" time frame of when a person could react" - every body is different and every body reacts whenever it is going to react, just because it's not "by the book" doesn't mean that our experience had nothing to do with this vaccine. My son reacted at day 4 and we were told a reaction usually occurs 7-10 days after..."by the book", therefore "no connection" I beg to differ. Why did his white blood cell count go so dangerously low? Why the fevers?
LAB_DATA: 3-27-07, WBC = 2.8; 4-3-07, WBC = 3.9; 4-17-07, WBC = 4; 6-3-07, WBC = 5; 4 - CBC blood/labs - for low white blood cell count

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (patient's mother) and refers to a 13 year old female patient. The patient's pertinent medical history and concurrent conditions were not reported. It was reported that the patient was accidentally given four doses of GARDASIL, intramuscularly, on 10-JUL-2008, 12-SEP-2008, 04-JAN-2009 and 24-JAN-2011. Exact dose, lot numbers and expiration dates were not provided for these vaccinations. The consumer reported that, on an unspecified date, her daughter experienced "adverse reactions starting with the first shot" (not specified which of them occurred after the first vaccination). The patient experienced fatigue, vomiting, nausea, migraines, chronic pain, and on an unknown date, she was diagnosed with dysautonomia, complex regional pain syndrome, celiac disease and postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (POTS). The patient was hospitalized in two hospitals (dates unspecified) and she was treated with unspecified pain medications. it was also reported, that the patient visited homeopathic doctor for detoxification (details unspecified). Laboratory diagnostic studies were performed: blood work, spinal tap, cat scan, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and numerous scopes (dates and detail were unspecified). The patient did not recover from dysautonomia, complex regional pain syndrome, celiac disease and postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (POTS). The relatedness between the events and GARDASIL was not reported. Additional information has been requested.
We called to schedule next set of shots and were informed that patient has died.

Initial unsolicited report received from a nurse on 30 July 2015. A ten years old female patient, whose medical history and concomitant medications were not reported, had received an intramuscular dose of ADACEL (batch number- C4774AA, exp. date: 15 July 2017) in left deltoid and an intramuscular dose of MENACTRA (batch number- U5155BA, exp. date: 13 January 2017) in right deltoid on 22 July 2015. The patient did not have any known allergies. Illness at the time of vaccination was reported as none. On 27 July 2015, five days after vaccination, the patient experienced Bell's Palsy. The patient required emergency room/doctor visit. Laboratory investigations were reported as none. Corrective treatments included Amoxicillin and Prednisone. At the time of this report, the patient had not recovered from the event. Upon medical review, the case was considered as serious due to important medical event: Bell's Palsy. Documents held by sender: none. Follow-up information received from physician on 24 August 2015. It was reported that other vaccination within 4 weeks prior to vaccination, illness at the time of vaccination was reported as none and pre-existing physician diagnosed allergies, birth defects and medical conditions was reported as mild intermittent asthma. The patient was vaccinated at private doctor's office/hospital and was purchased with private funds. Corrective treatments also included VALTREX. The patient's mother reported that the patient was recovering with some symptoms of Palsy but improvement and was expected to recover over next few weeks.
HISTORY: The patient did not have known allergies and illness at time of vaccination. Mild intermittent asthma.

Initial unsolicited report received from a pharmacist in the United States on 08 December 2015. This case involves 68-years-old female patient who was vaccinated with a dose of Fluzone HD batch number, dose in series were unknown and dose, expiry date were not reported) intramuscularly in right deltoid on 04 December 2015. Illness at time of vaccination and pre-existing physician diagnosed allergies, birth defects, medical conditions were reported as unknown. On an unknown date, following the vaccination, the patient had developed internal radiating pain to the shoulder. It was reported that no injection site redness, swelling or pain. The patient's laboratory data corrective treatment was not reported. The patient was not recovered from the event. Follow-up information received from a pharmacist on 11 January 2016. Lot number and expiry date of Fluzone HD was reported as UI1513AA and 12 June 2016. Patient was vaccinated with the second dose of vaccine at pharmacy. Patient was previously vaccinated with a first dose of Fluzone HD on an unspecified date. Patient did not experience any other vaccinations four weeks prior to the current vaccination. On an unspecified date, patient experienced pain and inflammation in her shoulder. It was stated that even one week post vaccination after usage of Ibuprofen regularly for a week, she went to physician who prescribed a 6 day regimen of a Medrol dose pack for the pain and inflammation in her shoulder and when that regimen was finished patient started Cyclobenzaprine, a muscle relaxant for a few days until the pain was resolved and was assisted by an accopantonist. On an unspecified date, patient recovered from the event pain and outcome of the event inflammation was not reported. List of documents held by sender: none.

C/O ITCHING IN RT ANTICUBITAL, THEN LEFT WITH ERYTHEMA, HIVES, WHEAL AND ITCHINESS ON BACK AND FRONT OF TORSO.  NO DIFFICULTY BREATHING.  50 MG BENADRYL GIVEN IM, SYMPTOMS SUBSIDED IN 20 MINUTES.
Rash, hives, swelling (all very severe requiring medication).
5-6 vesicular lesions-2 on back, one on head, on face, one on leg.  One lesion on back was large and surrounded by erythema.
LAB_DATA: IgM varicella positive.  IgM was negative.

HISTORY: Glaucoma, hypertension, diabetes type 2, high cholesterol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Redness, swelling, hotness in the area of vaccine injection.  Fever (subjective, unmeasured).
Severe swelling in left shoulder to elbow for one and a half weeks.

On November 7, 2015 I woke up with puffy eyelids, blurred vision and extreme photosensitivity.  I was also very tired.  I was evaluated by my doctor who was unsure if the Prevnar 13 vaccine was the reason for the symptoms.  He ordered labwork which essentially was normal.  He placed me on cortisone/antibiotic eyedrops as well as a Cortisone taper dose for 9 days.  I saw my optometrist for an eye check to see if he could determine the cause for the light sensitivity; he said my exam had not changed from August but thought there may be something systemic as the cause.  On November 30 I again saw my family doctor who referred me to my ophthalmologist.  I saw him on Dec. 7 and he said I had dry eyes and put me on drops.  I had never had dry eyes prior to this event.  Symptoms persisted so my doctor ordered an MRI of my brain which did not reveal any abnormality.  I am told I may have Sjogren's syndrome and it will take time for symptoms to improve. My activities of daily living are very impacted.  I know time has passed since the vaccine but I feel there is a direct correlation to the Prevnar 13 vaccine.
LAB_DATA: RBS:  96; MRI brain:  No abnormal findings

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 8:00 PM (~7 hours after administration of rabies vaccine #2), I developed systemic myalgias and arthralgias, headache, and rigors. The symptoms worsened over the next hour, so I took ibuprofen and went to bed. I woke up in the middle of the night (~3 AM) with persistent symptoms that had not lessened in severity. I took ibuprofen again and went back to sleep. When I awoke around 7 AM, the symptoms had resolved. Of note, I had received the first injection of the rabies vaccination series the week prior and had no adverse reaction.
HISTORY: Seasonal allergies only. No known drug allergies.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came back about thirty to forty minutes after vaccination stating severe itching.  Upon visual inspection there was redness (about size of fifty cent piece). Gave patient an ice pack to place on area and recommended Benadryl.  He held ice pack for 15 minutes and took Benadryl patient said symptoms improved.  Felt fine to go home.  Educated patient on signs and symptoms of anaphylaxis.  Called patient at 7:00PM (6 hours after) and he said he was just fine.

He woke up the next morning with soreness and redness at the site of the injection (Left Deltoid). He had a doctor appointment that morning for an unrelated situation and the MD told him it looked like cellulitis and that he should go to the hospital.
LAB_DATA: He said they gave him Keflex and are starting him on "2 broad spectrum antibiotics". His fever is down from 102.5 to 99.5.
OTHER_MEDS: Clorazepate 7.5mg QID PRN; Terazosin 5mg QD; Lisinopril 40mg QD; Amlodipine 10mg QD

This case was reported by a pharmacist via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of pulmonary embolism in a 42-year-old female patient who received ENGERIX B adult. The patient's past medical history included road traffic accident (Leg swelling) and female sterilization. Previously administered products included ENGERIX B adult (1st dose received on 20th August 2014) and ENGERIX B adult (2nd dose received on 17th September 2014). Concurrent medical conditions included hypertension and obesity. On 28th January 2015, the patient received the 3rd dos of ENGERIX B adult. On 28th January 2015, an unknown time after receiving ENGERIX B adult, the patient experienced drug dose administration interval too short. In February 2015, the patient experienced pulmonary embolism (serious criteria hospitalization and GSK medically significant) and chest pain. On 16th February 2015, the patient experienced shortness of breath. On an unknown date, the patient experienced iron deficiency anemia and pre-diabetes. The patient was treated with acetaminophen, LOVENOX, ferrous sulfate and Warfarin. On an unknown date, the outcome of the pulmonary embolism was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the shortness of breath, chest pain, iron deficiency anemia, pre-diabetes and drug dose administration interval too short were unknown. The reporter considered the pulmonary embolism to be possibly related to ENGERIX B adult. It was unknown if the reporter considered the shortness of breath, chest pain, iron deficiency anemia and pre-diabetes to be related to ENGERIX B adult. Additional details were received as follows: The blinded study vaccine was confirmed to be the ENGERIX B adult. Patient was 42-year-old, woman, who was enrolled in the other manufacturer's sponsored study. The patient was involved in a car accident prior to the study enrollment. The patient was in a rehabilitation facility, the exact injury that resulted in leg swelling was unknown, but it was confirmed that the time of immobility occurred prior to the onset of the pulmonary embolism. The site stated that no additional information was available. The patient had no previous history of deep vein thrombosis (DVT), smoking, or recent travel. It was unknown if there was a family history of DVT. The patient was not taking any oral or transdermal contraceptives nor hormonal replacement therapy. There were no concomitant medications in relation to pulmonary embolism. On 28th January 2015, the patient received the third dose of blinded study vaccine (ENGERIX B adult), which led to shortening of the vaccination schedule. On 16th February 2015, 20 days after having received the most recent dose (3rd dose) of study vaccine, the patient presented to the hospital with shortness of breath. The patient reported leg swelling and chest pain for the past two weeks. A chest x-ray showed no acute disease and no significant interval changes. A computerized tomography angiogram (CTA) chest showed left upper lobe and probable left lower lobe non-occlusive pulmonary emboli. Clot burden was low, otherwise no evidence acute disease of chest. A venous ultrasound bilateral lower extremity was normal without any evidence of thrombophlebitis. Her international normalized ratio was 1.1, haemoglobin was 11.1, and haematocrit was 35.5. She was found to have pulmonary embolism and was admitted to the hospital for further management. On 17th February 2015, warfarin dosing consultation was obtained as the international normalized ratio levels were sub therapeutic. She was started on LOVENOX and COUMADIN until the International normalized ratio was greater than 2. Further workup included lupus anticoagulant, antiphospholipid antibody, factor V Leiden mutation and prothrombin mutation, which were all reported to be negative (copies of results were unavailable). During the course of the hospitalization the patient had (glycosylated haemoglobin) HbA 1 c of 6.1 percent and was diagnosed with pre-diabetes (a medically
LAB_DATA: The CTA chest (CT angiography scan of chest) revealed that left upper lobe and probable left lower lobe nonocclusive pulmonary emboli. Clot burden is low. No evidence of acute disease of chest. The venous Doppler ultrasound bilateral lower extremities revealed that, normal without any evidence of thrombophlebitis. The factor V Leiden mutation was negative. The patient's prothrombin mutation was negative. The patient's fecal occult test was negative. 02/2015, Antiphospholipid antibodies, Negative; 02/2015, Blood thyroid stimulating hormone, normal; 02/16/2015, Chest X-ray, No acute disease and interval change; 02/2015, Glycosylated haemoglobin, 6.1%; 02/16/2015, Haematocrit, 35.5%; 02/20/2015, Haematocrit, 31.6%; 02/16/2015, Haemoglobin, 11.

The patient was vaccinated with FLUVIRIN (batch number: 173989) intramuscularly into left arm on 21 Oct 2015. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Flu symptoms, severe migraine from morning to night for both days more severe than usual chronic pain, muscle pain (arms, legs chest/shoulder area) arm swelling at the site of injection, weakness, excruciating toothache, facial pain, swelling, stiff neck. Infection in tooth, gums, sinus, and ear followed shortly after immunization. Complained to doctor staff, was told it was probably a reaction to the doses of two immunizations that I received. That it may have just been "too much for me" Treatment at emergency dentist of Amoxicillin in month of November. Again in December; Amox again, even though I explain to all docs that I am already resistant to two unknown (I forgot) types of antibiotics...then to ER for facial swelling and severe pain, migraine, infections, dehydration; diagnosed w/all but migraine and prescribed clindamycin. Infection not gone. To this day 02/04/2016 I have a reoccurring cyst in my gums, tooth abscess, persistent sinus infection and swelling which won't go away. My children have all caught the flu despite their own flu shots..(physicians) are not readily willing test or confirm the presence of MRSA. We are given antibiotics without bloodwork or nasal swabs to confirm anything. My 8 yr old daughter now has a lung infection with severe chest pain, diarrhea, dehydration, stomach pain, missing school. Her older brother (13 yrs) has type one diabetes with a fever of high as 103 degrees last weekend which got better with close monitoring and medicine, no doctor visit or ER, oldest son (15yrs) was very sick for one week in January, did not get treated or diagnosed, had the flu. Youngest son 10 yrs old had all flu symptoms with difficulty breathing, taken to doctor, given antibiotics as well as Pepto Bismol for throat, Tylenol and Motrin for severe fever of 104, Benadryl for sinusitis, it seems to have gone. Whatever has happened with the virus or whatever this is, our family can't seem to shake it and are all worsening, passing it back and forth and missing school, activities and going to a lot of doctor visits. I'm not understanding why blood testing is becoming a thing of the past nowadays to rule out more serious deficiency or autoimmune disorders which would make these occurrences more easily treated with knowledge of resistance.
HISTORY: Epilepsy, Chronic Migraines, TMJ problems, latex allergy, Vicodin allergy

This case was reported by a pharmacist via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of complex partial seizures in a 53-year-old female patient who received ENGERIX B adult. The patient's past medical history included hysterectomy and hip arthroplasty. Concurrent medical conditions included hypertension, osteoarthritis, fibromyalgia, hyperlipidemia, hypoglycemia, otitis externa, myositis, obesity, alcohol use (3 to 5 times per week), glucose tolerance impaired, myalgia, pain, fatigue, nausea, arthralgia, muscle weakness, depression, melanocytic nevus, hemorrhoids, rash, memory impairment, insomnia, amnesia, feeling abnormal and drug hypersensitivity (rash/hives). Concomitant products included ENGERIX B adult, gabapentin, pravastatin, fluticasone, salsalate, Amoxicillin-Clavulanate, hydrochlorothiazide + losartan, nortriptyline and CIPRODEX. On 15th September 2014, the patient received ENGERIX B adult. In September 2014, less than a month after receiving ENGERIX B adult, the patient experienced complex partial seizures (serious criteria hospitalization, GSK medically significant and other: As per reporter), consciousness disturbed (serious criteria GSK medically significant) and confusion. On 14th November 2014, the patient experienced blackout spell (serious criteria GSK medically significant). The patient was treated with KEPPRA, ferrous sulfate and TYLENOL. On an unknown date, the outcome of the complex partial seizures and blackout spell were unknown and the outcome of the consciousness disturbed and confusion were recovered/resolved. The reporter considered the complex partial seizures to be possibly related to ENGERIX B adult. It was unknown if the reporter considered the consciousness disturbed, blackout spell and confusion to be related to ENGERIX B adult. Additional details were received as follows: The blinded study vaccine was confirmed to be ENGERIX B adult. Patient was 53 years old woman, who was enrolled in the other manufacturer's sponsored study. The patient experienced an important medical event of complex partial seizures and was hospitalized. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initial unsolicited report received from a nurse via (other company Pfizer manufacturer number 2015443993) on 21 December 2015. This case involves a (61-year-old) female patient who was vaccinated with a dose of INFLUENZA VACCINE (FLU VACCINE) (batch number, expiry date, route of administration were not reported) in arm and also received a dose of PNEUMOCOCCAL POLYSACCHARIDE VACCINE (PREVNAR 13) (manufacturer Pfizer, batch number, expiry date, route of administration were not reported) in deltoid on 04 December 2015. Patient has medical history of rheumatoid arthritis. Patient had no vaccine given 4 weeks prior. On 04 December 2015, few hours "the same evening after getting the vaccine" following the vaccination patient experienced shortness of breath and feeling that she cannot get a lot of air. On December 2015, "after two or three days later" patient experienced headache, fatigue and increased joint pain. Patient did not required emergency room or doctors visit. Laboratory investigation and corrective treatment were not reported. The outcome of event was not recovered. Causality was reported as related "yes" for events shortness of breath and unknown for Headache, Fatigue and Increased joint pain. List of documents held by sender: none. Follow-up information received from a physician on 12 January 2016. Patient had received intramuscular dose of INFLUENZA QUADRIVAL A-B MULTIDOSE VACCINE PRESERVED (Fluzone) (batch number- UI431AB, expiry date- 06-Jan-2016) in left deltoid and an intramuscular dose of prevenar 13 (batch number- L99271, expiry date- 03-Mar-2017) in right deltoid on 4 December 2015 at 11:55 and 11:56 AM. Patient had no illness at the time of vaccination. Patient had a history of allergy to sulfa (January 2001), allergy to atorvastatin (October 2014), mild renal insufficiency (December 2001), reactive airway disease (October 2008), respiratory problems, wheezing, decreased memory and work. Patient was vaccinated at private physician's office/hospital. On 05 December 2015, one day after vaccination, patient experienced increased joint pain, headache and fatigue. The patient did not require any specific tests and treatments. Patient stated that she was recovering from the events but the symptoms were not totally gone and she said that her lungs were clear.

Hence, this case will be deactivated.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was feeling fine and then all of a sudden from one split second to the next I was instantly in pain, weak, dizzy, overall feeling of death sick, I had to get into bed before I collapsed.  I was not able to move, I was not able to take care of myself, I could not wake up, I could not reach for the glass of water that was 12 inches away from me, I was hot, feverish, sweaty and chills, I could barely get up to go to the bathroom, but because I was not eating or drinking I only urinated once in the morning and once in the evening. I finally went to the emergency on day 4, I had not changed my clothes at all during this time, the doctor at the emergency said I did not test positive for the flu, well that was not just the sniffles I received an IV, I was so incredibly weak. I felt like I was dying. I went home with no answers from the doctor. I still did not take or change my clothes until day 6. The flu vaccine I received from my place of employment,  I was told it was the Cadillac version and was very lucky to get it, as it was the quad dose. I will never never get a flu vaccine again.
LAB_DATA: Test came back as negative for the flu
CUR_ILL: Very sore arm, seemed more than usual

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My daughter was very warm at the injection site.  She was very irritable and red. There was excessive crying for about 3 to 4 hours.  Nothing that I would do seemed to comfort her.  I did call the after hours doctor's phone number to express my concern and was told that this was normal, but if she continued the following day, to bring her to the hospital.  Her symptoms seemed to get better and she was no longer crying the following day.  Her subsequent well baby visits demonstrated that she was growing well and seemed to be hitting her milestones. A year later, she was walking, but did not typically meet her milestones at 2 years (saying two to three words in a sentence) and was not sociable.  I did enroll her in an Early Intervention Program at age 3, and she was officially diagnosed with PDD/Autism at the same age by the Psychologist associated with the program, and a Developmental Pediatrician.  She is 17 years old now and attends a residential school.
LAB_DATA: Patient was tested for Fragile X, which turned out to be negative. MRI of the brain - normal. EEG test for 2 hours while napping - normal.
OTHER_MEDS: Pediatric liquid suspension (Tylenol) before vaccination and a few hours after.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This retrospective pregnancy case was reported by a pharmacist via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of Ebstein's anomaly in a female infant exposed to ENGERIX B adult in utero. The mother received the product. The parent's medical history included environmental allergy, attention deficit/hyperactivity disorder, normal birth (had 2 prior pregnancies), contraceptive (had been using condoms with spermicide for contraception), ENGERIX B adult (1st dose received on 14th August 2014) and ENGERIX B adult (2nd dose received on 11th September 2014). On 29th January 2015, the 36-year-old mother received the 3rd dose of ENGERIX B adult. The mother's last menstrual period was on 5th February 2015 and estimated date of delivery was 2nd November 2015. At 38 weeks and 2 days, the infant was born via vaginal delivery and weighed 3430 grams (7lbs 9oz) at birth. APGAR score was 8. The infant was diagnosed with Ebstein's anomaly (serious criteria GSK medically significant and congenital anomaly). On an unknown date, the infant experienced maternal vaccine exposure. On an unknown date, the outcome of the Ebstein's anomaly and maternal vaccine exposure was unknown. The reporter considered the Ebstein's anomaly to be possibly related to ENGERIX B adult. Additional details were received as follows: The blinded study vaccine was confirmed to be ENGERIX B adult. The patient's mother was 36 years old was enrolled in study. While enrolled in the study, the mother became pregnant and the baby (patient) was born with Ebstein's anomaly, mild, which was considered a birth defect. The patient's mother did not use benzodiazepines or lithium prior to or during pregnancy, had no dysrhythmia, and no toxic occupational exposure. The investigator did not consider the patent foramen ovale as a separate serious adverse event as it was part of the Ebstein's anomaly and would perinatal take a while to close. Relevant medical history of mother included two prior pregnancies, environmental allergies (1994), being overweight (30th July 2014), and ADHD (attention deficit/hyperactivity disorder). The mother of the patient had been using condoms with spermicide for contraception. The mother had no pregnancy risk factors. Family history was negative for congenital anomalies, sudden death, arrhythmia, dilated cardiomyopathy, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy, and premature coronary artery disease. The mother held a number of jobs and had been in contract analysis for 15 years, she had no toxic occupational exposure. The mother had no dysrhythmia, and had no exposure to benzodiazepines or lithium prior to or during the pregnancy. The mother was not taking any medications at the time of conception. The mother's last menstrual period (LMP) was on 5th February 2015 and the estimated conception date (ECD) was 11th February 2015. On 29th January 2015, the mother received 3rd dose of ENGERIX B adult. On 10th April 2015, the mother started taking clindamycin and an unspecified vaginal cream for bacterial vaginosis and INTEGRA PLUS for anaemia. On 16th April 2015, the patient had a positive pregnancy test. On 27th April 2015, the patient had a positive serum pregnant test. The estimated delivery date (EDD) was 2nd November 2015 (Pregnancy Report MCN 2015US003436). On 20th July 2015, it was reported that the mother's pregnancy was approximately at midterm and that she was doing well with no problems. 275 days after having received the third dose of blinded study vaccine (ENERGIX B adult), the mother vaginally delivered a live female infant (patient) at 39 weeks gestational age (full term). The infant's (patient) birth weight was 7 pounds and 9 ounces, the infant was 20.5 inches in length, head circumference was 14 inches. The Apgar score was 8 (assessed by the investigator as good). A cardiac murmur was auscultated at the time of birth and an echocardiogram showed moderate tricuspid valve regurgitation and poor mobility of the septal leaflet of the tricuspid valve, suspicious

This case was reported by a pharmacist via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of atrial flutter in a 53-year-old male patient who received ENGERIX B adult. On 1st October 2014, the patient received the 2nd dose of ENGERIX B adult. In October 2014, less than a month after receiving ENGERIX B adult, the patient experienced deep vein thrombosis (serious criteria GSK medically significant), acute renal failure (serious criteria GSK medically significant) and hepatic cirrhosis (serious criteria GSK medically significant). On 20th October 2014, the patient experienced atrial flutter (serious criteria hospitalization and other: As per reporter), respiratory failure (serious criteria GSK medically significant), hypertension aggravated, tachycardia and chest pain. On an unknown date, the patient experienced type II diabetes mellitus (serious criteria GSK medically significant), ascites (serious criteria GSK medically significant), bladder disorder, pulmonary effusion and lethargy. The patient was treated with COUMADIN, carvedilol, VICTOZA, NOVOLOG, Sliding Scale Insulin, LANTUS, amiodarone and lisinopril. On an unknown date, the outcome of the atrial flutter, deep vein thrombosis, acute renal failure, respiratory failure, hypertension aggravated and bladder disorder were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the hepatic cirrhosis, type II diabetes mellitus, ascites, pulmonary effusion, lethargy, tachycardia and chest pain were unknown. The reporter considered the atrial flutter, acute renal failure, hepatic cirrhosis, type II diabetes mellitus, respiratory failure, hypertension aggravated and bladder disorder to be unrelated to ENGERIX B adult. The reporter considered the deep vein thrombosis to be possibly related to ENGERIX B adult. It was unknown if the reporter considered the ascites, pulmonary effusion, lethargy, tachycardia and chest pain to be related to ENGERIX B adult. Additional details were received as follows: The blinded study vaccine was confirmed to be ENGERIX B adult. The patient was 53 years old man, who was enrolled in the other manufacturer's sponsored study. Relevant medical history included chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) (1990), kidney stones (1992), osteoarthritis in bilateral hands (2009), bilateral pedal edema (2011), reactive airway disease (2011), and hypertension (2012). It was noted that the subject was homeless and lived out of his car. Relevant concomitant medications included multivitamin, ibuprofen and DULERA. On 3rd September 2014, the patient received 1st dose of blinded study vaccine (ENGERIX B adult). On 1st October 2014, the patient received 2nd dose of blinded study vaccine (ENGERIX B adult). On 20th October 2014, 19 days after the most recent dose of blinded study vaccine (ENGERIX B adult), the patient went to his primary care physician (PCP) for the evaluation of chest pain and he was advised to go to the hospital. The site confirmed that the outcome of the event cirrhosis will remain unchanged and that the subject reported that his deep vein thrombosis was asymptomatic. The deep vein thrombosis (DVT) was discovered during testing while the subject was hospitalized, that the DVT was treated with heparin while hospitalized and that the patient was discharged on COUMADIN. The site confirmed that the history of "stones" referred to kidney stones. Corrected adverse events form for the event of deep vein thrombosis, confirming the onset date as 23-Oct-2014 and the investigator's assessment of relationship to study vaccine as possibly related. The site stated that they would provide an update after the subject had completed the week 56 site visit to clarify the outcome status of the events of cirrhosis, focal thickening on the posterior wall of the urinary bladder, and type II diabetes. The updated outcome and end date for the event of focal thickening on the posterior wall of the urinary bladder (resolved on 4th December 2014), and updated outcomes for the events of cirrhosi
